    More Info on Spain La Liga

    What is Spain La Liga?

    La Liga is a football domestic league competition held annually in Spain. The current La Liga season is 2023/24. La Liga is the 1st division in Spain. This means that the league is 1st in the domestic pyramid. 380 matches are currently scheduled in total, and so far 340 fixtures have been completed with 890 goals have been scored in aggregate. 20 teams are competing for the title this season.

    What are the recent Spain La Liga results?

    The latest results in La Liga are : Sevilla FC vs Granada CF (Ended 3 - 0), Rayo Vallecano vs UD Almería (Ended 0 - 1), Valencia CF vs Deportivo Alavés (Ended 0 - 1). The last fixture was played on May 5, 2024. For the rest of the results of matches in this season, please visit our results and fixtures list.

    Which fixtures are upcoming in Spain La Liga?

    The next fixtures in La Liga are : Deportivo Alavés vs Girona FC (May 10), Real Club Deportivo Mallorca vs UD Las Palmas (May 10), Villarreal CF vs Sevilla FC (May 10). There are 40 matches left to play in this La Liga season with possibly more fixtures being scheduled. Go to the full calendar of Spain La Liga fixtures to see the entire list.

    Who is the table leader in Spain La Liga?

    In the current 2023/24 season, Real Madrid CF is 1st in the La Liga table with 87 points from 34 matches played. This is from 27 wins, 6 draws, and 1 losses. Real Madrid CF scored 74 goals and conceded 22 goals in the process. Their average points per game is 2.56 across the entire 2023/24 season.

    Girona FC is 2nd in the La Liga table with 74 points earned. This puts them 13 points behind 1st place Real Madrid CF and 1 points in front of 3rd place FC Barcelona.

    What's the Match Attendance in Spain La Liga like?

    An average of 31,349 people attend each fixture in Spain La Liga. For more attendance specific data, visit La Liga Attendance list.

    Who are the Top Scorers in Spain La Liga?

    La Liga players with the most goals in the 2023/24 are : Artem Dovbyk (20 goals), Jude Bellingham (18 goals), Alexander Sørloth (17 goals), Robert Lewandowski (17 goals), Ante Budimir (16 goals), Borja Mayoral (15 goals), Alvaro Morata (14 goals), Gorka Guruzeta (14 goals), Antoine Griezmann (13 goals), Youssef En-Nesyri (13 goals), and Hugo Duro (13 goals).

    The teams that are scoring really well at the moment are : Real Madrid CF with 74 goals scored (43 at home and 31 at away), Girona FC with 73 goals scored (46 at home and 27 at away), FC Barcelona with 70 goals scored (38 at home and 32 at away), and Club Atlético de Madrid with 63 goals scored (40 at home and 23 at away).

    At home venues, the teams that are the top of the scoring table are : Girona FC with 46 home goals, Real Madrid CF with 43 home goals, Club Atlético de Madrid with 40 home goals, and FC Barcelona with 38 home goals.

    Away from home, the top scoring teams are : Girona FC with 27 away goals, Real Madrid CF with 31 away goals, Club Atlético de Madrid with 23 away goals, and FC Barcelona with 32 away goals.

    Zespoły, które obecnie dobrze bronią się w La Liga, to: UD Almería z 67 straconymi bramkami (33 u siebie i 34 na wyjeździe), Granada CF z 64 straconymi bramkami (26 u siebie i 38 na wyjeździe), Villarreal CF z 58 straconych bramek (26 u siebie i 32 na wyjeździe) oraz Real Club Celta de Vigo z 52 straconymi bramkami (20 u siebie i 32 na wyjeździe).

    Zespoły, które zachowały najwięcej czystych kont w La Liga to: Real Madryt CF z 18 czystymi kontami, Athletic Club Bilbao z 16 czystymi kontami, FC Barcelona z 14 czystymi kontami i Real Sociedad de Fútbol z 13 czystymi kontami.
